9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 764, L.D. 1159, “An Act to Prohibit
10 Businesses from Refusing to Accept Cash for In-person Payments”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Prohibit Governmental Entities That Charge a Fee for In-person Credit
13 Card Purchases from Refusing to Accept Cash'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 10 MRSA c. 239 is enacted to read:
17 CHAPTER 239
18 PAYMENT BY CASH
19 §1500-Y. Payment by cash
20 A municipality or other governmental entity offering goods or services for sale at retail
21 that charges a customer a fee on purchases made by credit card may not refuse payment in
22 the form of cash for the goods or services.
23 For purposes of this section, "sale at retail" means any retail transaction conducted in
24 person and does not include a transaction conducted remotely by telephone, mail or the
25 Internet.'
26 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
27 number to read consecutively.
28 SUMMARY
2299 This amendment, which is a minority report of the committee, replaces the bill and
3300 changes the title. The amendment requires municipalities or other governmental entities
